    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Wordpress : ne plus avoir de texte qui déborde avec la balise "pre"]]></title>
    <link href="http://tym-project.github.com/2009/11/17/wordpress-ne-plus-avoir-de-texte-qui-deborde-avec-la-balise-pre/"/>
    <updated>2009-11-17T12:35:53+00:00</updated>
    <id>http://tym-project.github.com/2009/11/17/wordpress-ne-plus-avoir-de-texte-qui-deborde-avec-la-balise-pre</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>J'utilise énormément la balise <code>pre</code>, qui
permet d'afficher du code (scripts...) de manière lisible et surtout détachée
du texte. Mais cette méthode à un inconvénient majeur : si la ligne est trop
longue elle va tout simplement dépasser du "cadre", et aller baver sur le menu
de droite par exemple. Il existe une petite astuce en CSS pour résoudre ce
problème, attention les yeux... Vous devez utiliser le code suivant :
<div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'> <div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='css'><span class='line'><span class="nt">white-space</span><span class="o">:</span> <span class="nt">pre-wrap</span><span class="o">;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">/&lt;</span><span class="nt">em</span><span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="nt">css-3</span> <span class="o">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">em</span><span class="o">&gt;/</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">white-space</span><span class="o">:</span> <span class="nt">-moz-pre-wrap</span> <span class="o">!</span><span class="nt">important</span><span class="o">;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">/&lt;</span><span class="nt">em</span><span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="nt">Mozilla</span><span class="o">,</span> <span class="nt">since</span> <span class="nt">1999</span> <span class="o">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">em</span><span class="o">&gt;/</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">white-space</span><span class="o">:</span> <span class="nt">-pre-wrap</span><span class="o">;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">/&lt;</span><span class="nt">em</span><span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="nt">Opera</span> <span class="nt">4-6</span> <span class="o">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">em</span><span class="o">&gt;/</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">white-space</span><span class="o">:</span> <span class="nt">-o-pre-wrap</span><span class="o">;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">/&lt;</span><span class="nt">em</span><span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="nt">Opera</span> <span class="nt">7</span> <span class="o">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">em</span><span class="o">&gt;/</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="nt">word-wrap</span><span class="o">:</span> <span class="nt">break-word</span><span class="o">;</span>
</span><span class='line'><span class="o">/&lt;</span><span class="nt">em</span><span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="nt">Internet</span> <span class="nt">Explorer</span> <span class="nt">5</span><span class="nc">.5</span><span class="o">+</span> <span class="o">&lt;/</span><span class="nt">em</span><span class="o">&gt;/</span>
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div>
Après modification, au lieu de ça :</p>

<pre><code>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum et molestie sapien. Aliquam vel felis in massa bibendum iaculis sit amet nec tortor. 
</code></pre>

<p>Vous aurez ça :</p>

<pre><code>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum et molestie sapien. Aliquam vel felis in massa bibendum iaculis sit amet nec tortor. 
</code></pre>

<p><em>Comme je ne suis lpus sur Wordpress, l'exemple n'est plus du tout parlant... sorry !</em></p>

<p>Bon CSS ;-)</p>
